    <title>Combined summary - LOT=False is dangerous and shouldn't be used</title>
    <updated>2023-06-14T18:51:45.612781+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/bitcoin-dev/2021-March/018513.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The activation of the Taproot upgrade in Bitcoin has sparked controversy regarding the level of support required from miners for activation. The Lock In On Timeout (LOT) parameter has been suggested as a compromise, with LOT=True being viewed as the safest option to minimize risk to all users and the network. Some members of the bitcoin-dev mailing list have expressed concerns about relying solely on miner signaling to coordinate activation of protocol upgrades, as it leaves open the possibility of a miner veto, which puts the network at significant risk. Giving miners a veto creates an incentive to second-guess the decision to activate and/or hold the activation hostage, which is why it's important to avoid a chain split.LOT=False, where Taproot will be activated if at least 95% of miners vote yes, has been compared to the LOT=true proposal, where Taproot will be activated if at least 0% of miners vote yes. However, this proposal has raised concerns about the potential for unreliable networks and chain splits with different levels of enforcement. Some users are concerned that those running LOT=False will face an unreliable chain if miners decide to produce a chain split, being replaced by the LOT=True chain every time it overtakes the LOT=False chain in work.In conclusion, LOT=True minimizes risk to everyone and has no risk to users running LOT=True, while LOT=False puts users and the network at significant risk in all possible scenarios. The overall risk is maximally reduced by LOT=True being the only deployed parameter, and any introduction of LOT=False only increases risk probability and severity. BIP 8 (LOT=True) combines the certainty of a flag day with the speed improvement of a MASF, so that soft forks can be activated both quickly and safely. It is important to avoid a chain split, and the purpose of supermajority signaling is to reduce the chance of it happening.</summary>
